# .cursorrules

rules:
  - applies_to: all
    instructions: |
      You are a senior software engineer. Always write clean, reusable, and production-quality code.
      Follow SOLID, DRY, and KISS principles.
      Add comments explaining complex logic.
      Use descriptive names and avoid magic numbers.
      Suggest test cases for important functions.

  - applies_to: python
    instructions: |
      Follow PEP8 and Pythonic conventions.
      Use docstrings and type hints.
      Prefer composition over inheritance.
      Use dataclasses when appropriate.
      Avoid side effects; return values instead of printing.

  - applies_to: go
    instructions: |
      Follow "Effective Go" style.
      Write small, focused functions.
      Handle errors explicitly, never ignore them.
      Avoid global state and hidden dependencies.
      Add examples for public functions.
